data.text: @Ausshot3Dave Deregulation has been a huge success for money-loving corporatocracies. They get the freedom to do whatever they like to increase their profits bereft of responsibility to the society that makes it possible.

@bretthore91 Yes I’m the same & ever since I found out I’m very particular on everything in the supermarket. Only using Aldi at the moment as all items have no artificial flavours or colours. So they advertise anyway. A lot of the problems are these supermarket brands?

@Ausshot3Dave I cook & received a herb display/stand with about 18 types.
Check them all & kept the cinnamon sticks and pepper corns only.
None of the rest were right by smell or look, didn't risk taste.
Imagine living there & only having those choices, poor bastards.

@bretthore91 Yes it is mate. China had big problems with contaminated milk powder. Choice has uncovered here things like nearly all the oregano is substituted with grass and they have about 10 items of food contaminated. Food protection used to be controlled

@Ausshot3Dave We discovered the fake honey about 3 yrs ago when it started to crystallize back into sugar. 
Isn't it supposed to be a part of the governments protection role to ensure food safety & surety.
